United States Beat Israel 2-1 in Friendly 
Alexi Lalas scored his ninth international goal and Jovan Kirovski
scored his fourth as the United States defeated Israel 2-1 in a
friendly match Tuesday night.
The Americans scored first in the 28th minute when Alexi Lalas broke
free of an Israeli defender and deflected in Jeff Agoos' free kick.
Lalas' score held up until the 68th minute when Jovan Kirovski drilled
a shot past an outstretched Israeli backup goalkeeper Itzak Korenfain
to give the Americans a 2-0 lead.
Israel scored in the 82nd minute when Moshe Glan broke past a U.S.
defender and slipped a shot past the United States' goalie Juergen
Sommer.
